  "abstract": "Fusarium moniliforme Sheld. and\r\nMacrophomina phaseolina (Tassi) Goid\r\nare important soil-borne pathogens which\r\nattack a large number of crop plants. In\r\nmaize, they are known to cause stalk rots\r\nwhich take a heavy toll every year. Hitherto,\r\nthe control measures suggested for these\r\n~oil-borne fungi included mostly improved\r\ncultural practices. In recent years, several\r\nindustries have developed numerous soil\r\nfungicides, a few of which have proved\r\neconomical in controlling diseases of certain\r\nc!Ops in other countries. In the present\r\nstudy, an attempt was made to test\r\nthe efficacy of some of the fungicides against\r\nthese fungi both in vitro and in soil...",
